<paragraph id="DF56EA31FFFEFFA7FF43FEB18B84FDAF" blockId="75.[151,1436,338,847]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FF43FEB18AB1FE67" bold="true" box="[199,478,378,404]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
Among species with numerous setae on the wing membrane, uniformly colored abdomen, foretibial scale without spur, base of superior volsella without microtrichia, and base of superior volsella with 5 inner setae, the species can be distinguished by having inferior volsella with 2 apical setae and projection of the superior volsella with 2 lateral seta placed in apical half. 
<taxonomicName id="18E991B2FFFEFFA7FC78FE398E68FDF8" box="[1020,1287,498,524]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudosordens" subGenus="Pe.">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FC78FE398F64FDF8" box="[1020,1035,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FBA7FE398F2DFDF8" box="[1059,1090,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Pe</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FBDEFE398E68FDF8" box="[1114,1287,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">pseudosordens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and to some extent 
<taxonomicName id="18E991B2FFFEFFA7FF61FDD18AA6FDC0" baseAuthorityName="Sasa" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[229,457,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kasumiense" subGenus="Pe.">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FF61FDD18B9BFDC0" box="[229,244,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FE88FDD18A44FDC0" box="[268,299,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Pe</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FEC6FDD18AA6FDC0" box="[322,457,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">kasumiense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a superior volsella with two lateral setae, but these species differ in most other details.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FFFEFFA7FF43FDA18A31FD77" blockId="75.[151,1436,338,847]" box="[199,350,618,644]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FFFEFFA7FF43FDA18A69FD77" bold="true" box="[199,262,618,644]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Male</emphasis>
(n = 1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FFFEFFA7FF43FD598927FCD4" blockId="75.[151,1436,338,847]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<typeStatus id="00525493FFFEFFA7FF43FD598A5BFD5F" box="[199,308,658,684]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Holotype</typeStatus>
(slide) damaged. Thorax and abdominal segments dark brown. Wing lost. AR 1.5, LR 
<subScript id="436DE874FFFEFFA7FAA3FD698E40FD43" attach="left" box="[1319,1327,674,688]" fontSize="6" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">1</subScript>
1.9. Projection of superior volsella (
<figureCitation id="47D2F6B4FFFEFFA7FE66FD768926FD24" box="[482,585,701,727]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="53.[151,254,1631,1655]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,195,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-213@53.[245,1342,181,1693]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURE 15. Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) spp., males, anal point (C) and superior volsella. A—P. (Pe.) elongatus Tokunaga; B, C—P. (Pe.) kamosecundum (Sasa); D—P. (Pe.) mellense (Goetghebuer); E—P. (Pe.) nodosum (Johannsen); F—P. (Pe.) pseudosordens Zhang et Wang; G—P. (Pe.) palauensis Tokunaga; H—P. (Pe.) toyamadeeum (Sasa); I—P. (Pe.) tusimaefeum (Sasa); J—P. (Pe.) tusimafegeum (Sasa)." pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
) strongly curved with 2 lateral setae, base with 5 inner setae as opposed to the 3 inner setae indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="BB7897C0FFFEFFA7FD97FD2E886CFD0C" author="Goetghebuer, M." box="[531,771,741,767]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref91222" refString="Goetghebuer, M. (1942) Ceratopogonidae et Chironomidae nouveaux ou peu connus d'Europe. Bulletin du Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique, 18 (46), 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1942">Goetghebuer (1942)</bibRefCitation>
. Inferior volsella parallel-sided, with 2 long apical setae. Anal point tapering to parallel-sided.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
